result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis J. Warner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Arm Self w/ Dangerous Weapon [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(2)(b).
  • Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000 [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Restitution and costs have been paid from defendant's bond.  Restitution is joint and several.  The total restitution ordered was $7,626.63 plus restitution surcharge.  The co-defendant in Taylor County Case No. 15CF82 has paid $5,000.00 towards the restitution which leaves a balance owing of $2,626.63 plus restitution surcharge.

Defendant shall write a letter of apology to the victims, due within 30 days of plea and sentencing and preapproved by probation.  Defendant shall undergo any other counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.    Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA and follow through with any recommendations.

timeConds.notes:
The jail sentence shall begin no later than June 12, 2017.  The defendant shall pay all sheriff and jail fees or costs allowed or imposed by law and the sheriff shall be entitled to a judgment against the defendant for any such unpaid fees or costs.  
Jail can be served in any county in the State of Wisconsin provided arrangements are made by counsel or the defendant, it is approved by the Taylor County Jail, and at no additional cost to Taylor County.

Defendant Travis J. Warner in court with attorney Paul M Goetz.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record.  Victim rights have been complied.  One of the victims is present.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to count 1 - burglary, PTAC with the enhancer of for arming self with weapon.  Plea of no contest to count 3 - Theft, PTAC and no contest to count 5 - Theft, Special Facts, PTAC.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently.  Court finds defendant guilty of counts 1, 3 and 5.  Statement by the victim.  Statement by the defendant.  Court orders - count 1 - withheld sentence; probation for three years with conditions of 9 months county jail with huber to begin no later than June 12, 2017; court costs; AODA and comply with treatment recommendations; restitution joint and several; letter of apology to the victims due within 30 days of plea and sentencing to be preapproved by probation; any other counseling as deemed appropriate by probation. Court did not order a DNA sample and surcharge as it was previously order in Case No. 15CF77.   Count 3 - withheld sentence - probation for 3 years; with same conditions as count 1 with no additional jail.  Count 5 withheld sentence - probation for 3 years with same conditions as count 1, with no additional jail time.  The remaining counts are to be dismissed and read in.
